subsection Analytics

aftertext
 This site does not use cookies or include any tracking scripts. You can view a report of web traffic to this site <a href="nginxStats.html">here</a>.
 https://www.nginx.com/ NGINX

aftertext
 The log reports are generated using goaccess and is run once daily via the cron job below.
 https://goaccess.io/

cronCode
 0 5 * * * goaccess /var/log/nginx/access.log -o /var/www/html/nginxStats.html --log-format=COMBINED

subsection Server setup

bashCode
 ssh root@pldb.pub
 apt-get update
 apt-get upgrade
 reboot
 # Log back in:
 ssh root@pldb.pub
 adduser pldb
 usermod -aG sudo pldb
 su pldb
 cd
 sudo apt-get install nginx
 # google "digital ocean certbot" and follow instructions.
 # add the server stats cron job below with:
 crontab -e
 # Update nginx conf to allow CORS using the snippet below:
 vim /etc/nginx/nginx.conf
 sudo systemctl restart nginx
 # deploy the site to /var/www/html

aftertext
 CORS is enabled by putting the below code in our nginx config.

nginxConfigCode
 add_header 'Access-Control-Allow-Origin' '*' always;
 add_header 'Access-Control-Allow-Methods' 'GET, POST, OPTIONS' always;
 add_header 'Access-Control-Allow-Headers' 'DNT,User-Agent,X-Requested-With,If-Modified-Since,Cache-Control,Content-Type,Range' always;
 add_header 'Access-Control-Expose-Headers' 'Content-Length,Content-Range' always;

